Estonia Ministry Confirms Seven Citizens Kidnapped in Lebanon

-- B y   O t t   U m m e l a s
-- 
2011-03-24T06:31:36Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-24/estonia-ministry-confirms-seven-citizens-kidnapped-in-lebanon.html
Seven Estonian citizens have been
kidnapped in Lebanon, the Estonian Foreign Ministry said,
confirming media reports.  Foreign Minister Urmas Paet has formed a crisis committee
and has received a pledge to assist from the Lebanese
authorities, the ministry said in an e-mailed statement in
Tallinn today. Relatives of the missing nationals have been
contacted.  Lebanese security forces are searching for seven Estonians
and Ukrainians who were kidnapped after entering the east of the
country on bicycles from neighboring  Syria , Lebanonâ€™s official
National News Agency reported yesterday.  Armed assailants in two vans and a dark-colored Mercedes
without license plates ambushed the group and forced the Eastern
Europeans to go with them to the village of Kfar Zabad, NNA
said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
